1 conducting research projects or experiments.
2 “(7) A compact fluorescent lamp used to replace a lamp in a motor vehicle
3 manufactured on or before January 1, 2020.
4 “(8) A lamp purchased by a school district, as defined in ORS 332.002, or
5 an education service district, as defined in ORS 334.003, for use in buildings
6 used to provide educational services to students.
7 “(9) A lamp purchased by the owner or operator of one or more fa-
8 cilities located in this state that together comprise more than one
9 million square feet for use in the purchaser’s facility. For purposes
10 of this subsection, the square footage of buildings owned or operated
11 by the purchaser’s parent company or subsidiary, or by an entity that
12 is similarly related to the purchaser, may be used to determine the
13 total square footage of buildings owned or operated by the
14 purchaser.”.
